    "Let A be a semiabelian variety over k of dimension ≤ g. If A(k) has a non-torsion point (i.e., if rank(A(k)) ≥ 1) and m p ≥ 1 for infinitely many primes p, then the Mordell-Weil group A(K g,m) modulo the torsion subgroup A(K g,m) tor is not free.",
    "In particular, it is not finitely generated.",
    "This follows from the following lemma, since if P ∈ A(k) is a non-torsion point, then it is divisible by p mp (> 1) in A(K g,m) for infinitely many p.",
    "Let M be a Z-module.",
    "If there exist a non-zero element x of M and infinitely many positive integers d 1, d 2,."
  ]
